         <div>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">“Yan Ling Ji Zi, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">it is really the people of Heaven! </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">When he is born </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">he does not follow their customs. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">The people of Wu seven years after their birth </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">move and disperse, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en">and have their breasts painted, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en">but Yan Ling Ji Zi was proud </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en">and did not accept it. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en">Yan Ling Ji Zi, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en">it is really the people of Heaven! </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">Zi Gong [said]: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">what? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">The possession of humanity.” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">“It is placed at his bottom, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">he does not break his branches, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en">eats his fruits, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en">[does not destroy his tools].” [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">“I have heard that for the loss of the parents </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">he eats meat as if eating dirt, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">he drinks wine as if drinking a (dirty) mixture, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">is it true?” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">Zi Gong said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">“Nobody is more intimate than the parents, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">if one does not care when they die, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en">what would it be when they are still alive? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en">It is true.” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en">The master [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] You do not understand it? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">You! </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">Now to brave difficulties for the masses, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">to receive emoluments for your kin, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">to labor to accomplish affairs, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">to use official seals to serve as an official, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">for the shi to serve with energy, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en">then the sacrificial offerings </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] would not reign over it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">that is good, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">but now how can he reign over the people? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">You! </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">The master passed through Cao, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">Yan Yuan drove his carriage. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">He reached Lao Qiu (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en">there were peasants cultivating with their hoe </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en">and singing there (?). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">The master relies on models and [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">the tune, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">makes the rhythm chaotic </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">and the sound sad. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">The mourning of Cao, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">must it necessarily be like this?” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en">“Hui!” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en">Sighed the master: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-6a.9" xml:lang="en">“Oh! Nobody understands me!” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en">Zi You said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en">“Is this called to have a plan?” (?). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en">“Yan, I have not yet seen xx </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en">and trusted him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en">I have not yet seen somebody serving people well </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.7" xml:lang="en">and been worried. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-7a.8" xml:lang="en">The present age [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en">The master heard about it and said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en">“Ci, you do not understand me. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en">You rise early and go to bed late, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en">to obtain to hear [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en">[does not...to] approach people, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en">does not bend embankments to repel people.” ?? </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en">“The master has nothing which is not enough, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en">and nothing which is superfluous, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en">therefore [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.5" xml:lang="en">seeks to express it in words. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.6" xml:lang="en">Once he has the words, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.7" xml:lang="en">he seeks to enact them. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.8" xml:lang="en">When words and acts are close to each other, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-9a.9" xml:lang="en">then one acts like a gentleman.” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-10a.1" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-10a.2" xml:lang="en">“Hui! come, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-10a.3" xml:lang="en">I will tell you. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-10a.4" xml:lang="en">Have the obstacles been removed? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-10a.5" xml:lang="en">Even if one has heard many people, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-10a.6" xml:lang="en">but does not befriends worthies, his [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-10a.7" xml:lang="en">how (could it) end.” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.1" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.2" xml:lang="en">If one listens to few people, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.3" xml:lang="en">he is lonely, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.4" xml:lang="en">if one sees few things </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.5" xml:lang="en">he is lax. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.6" xml:lang="en">If one listens to (too) many people, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.7" xml:lang="en">he is perplexed, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-11a.8" xml:lang="en">if one sees (too) many things then [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] one accomplishes it after (due) consideration. ??? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.2" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.3" xml:lang="en">“Disciple, come, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.4" xml:lang="en">follow my words: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.5" xml:lang="en">old age does not always comes, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.6" xml:lang="en">and (anyway) when one is old he cannot recover his strength, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.7" xml:lang="en">worthies are anxious [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-12a.8" xml:lang="en">[...] there. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en">"as for people humble and poor </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en">who are not compliant, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en">I have seen them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en">but as for people with honors and riches </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en">not being proud. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en">I have heard about them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.8" xml:lang="en">but I have not yet seen them. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.9" xml:lang="en">As for officials [...], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.10" xml:lang="en">I have seen them; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.11" xml:lang="en">but (those) serving </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.12" xml:lang="en">and not receiving (emoluments) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.13" xml:lang="en">I have heard about them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-13a.14" xml:lang="en">but I have not yet seen them. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-14a.1" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en">“For a (humane) person to approach those below himself, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-14a.3" xml:lang="en">is like approaching those above himself.” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-15a.1" xml:lang="en">He said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-15a.2" xml:lang="en">“Smart words and attractive appearance </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-15a.3" xml:lang="en">are not enough to be called humanity. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en">[.] his words, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-15a.5" xml:lang="en">cannot but be [.]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-15a.6" xml:lang="en">[...] this can be called humanity. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-16a.1" xml:lang="en">Zai Wo asked about the gentleman. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en">He said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en">“Yu! If you can be attentive to the beginning as well as to the end (of an affair), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en">this is good, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en">(but) can this be considered to act like a gentleman? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en">How could you?” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-17a.1" xml:lang="en">Xxx stopping ??? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-17a.2" xml:lang="en">the master is so sincere, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-17a.3" xml:lang="en">hearing Zi Lu going (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-17a.4" xml:lang="en">the master is so majestic; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0055_tls_001-17a.5" xml:lang="en">if he punishes [...] </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
